Definition: in an ardent manner
Example: the spirit of God knew very well that there was a deeper question to be settled before there could be the intervention in power that was so ardently desired
Synonyms: adj, all, passionate, ardent, in, an, manner, the, spirit, of, God, knew, very, well, that, there, was, a, deeper, question, to, be, settled, before, could, intervention, power, so, desired
Category: adv.all
